profile_positions.description:
In this role I was mainly responsible for managing the day to day operations of the team (7-9 Content Executives) including recruitment, performance management, workload distribution, reporting & project coordination.

	Main Achievements 
Success in the role meant the team was able to meet business and stakeholder expectations in terms of due date delivery and quality of work.
As a leader for this team my personal achievement has been to develop an empowered, self-sustaining and high-performing team.
During this time I have also successfully developed and implemented a Quality Assessment Framework for Photo Moderation activities.

	Also responsible for:
Stakeholder management;
Increasing visibility of the team in the wider business;
Supporting team development through workshops and offsites;
Change management;
Assisting in additional projects based on business needs.

Leading a team of 15-19 multilingual Customer Service Executives with an energetic, open-minded manner towards achieving goals and developing their skills continuously, while supporting the wider operation by leading various projects and initiatives.

Main Achievements
Leading a high performing team through extensive periods of change, challenging and empowering team members to build further on their strengths and develop on their improvement areas;
Created and implemented an improved and more efficient payroll process, currently used for the entire site consisting of more than 500 employees;
Actively supported an internal development program through mentoring leadership workshops as well as giving input to the further improvement of the program;
Created and delivered a workshop aimed at developing analytical skills among fellow team leaders; facilitated several sessions on a regional scale (EMEA);
Developed and facilitated a training program for the support staff of two new call centre locations;
Leading an additional project team working on requests with a higher level of complexity.

Also responsible for:
Coaching team members and peers;
Assure strong quality as well as productivity standards within the team;
Track and monitor performance levels, and manage underperformance;
Conduct monthly 1-2-1 meetings with CSEs to maintain focus and motivation on Customer Service standards and targets;
Prepare and conduct quarterly performance reviews and keep track of progress during the year;
Manage escalated complaints by phone and e-mail;
Being an effective Change Manager, who knows how to handle periods of change and lead a team through such periods, displaying motivating and encouraging behaviors;
Collaborating with HR in the recruitment process of new employees;
Replacing and carrying out activities of other Team Leads or the Customer Service Manager if needed;
Assist in additional tasks and projects if needed.

Main responsibilities:
Advise and coach customer and accommodation service executives;
Track and solve massive complaints and escalations by working together with accommodation partners and other departments;
Proactive in developing projects aimed to improve current processes towards efficiency;
Assisting in additional tasks and projects, such as recruitment and workshops;

Main responsibilities consisted of:
Liaising between the guest and accommodation when handling special requests and complaints by phone and e-mail;
Delivering high level of customer service through clear communication, problem-solving and negotiating skills;
Ownership in ensuring follow up and first contact resolution in each interaction resulting in excellent customer experiences;
Actively participating in various projects within the department.
